See https://www1.grc.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/C3.3_Ames.pdf

For non-diffusive problem, the flow can be reversed. So one can advance with dt and then -dt, and re-generate initial condition. 
This can be done in Advance.cpp

See the following for more details:
(1) "Time-reversibility of the Euler equations as a benchmark for energy conserving schemes" https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0021999108003422
(2) "Benchmarks for the Transport Equation: The Convection‚ÄêDiffusion Forum and Beyond" https://agupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1029/CE047p0241
